The paper deals with wireless networks and the analysis of the Signal-to-Interference-plus-Noise-Ratio (SINR) and spectral efficiency of links with multi-antenna receivers. This falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) categories. The paper also uses asymptotic techniques and power-law node intensities, which are common in the Mathematics of Computing (cs.MA) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the benefit of using antenna arrays in non-homogeneous wireless networks, which could be relevant to the Performance (cs.PF) category.
